[03:05.77]“Then I saw that the gallery ran down at last into a thick darkness.  I hesitated, and then, as I looked round me, I saw that the dust was less abundant and its surface less even.  Further away towards the dimness, it appeared to be broken by a number of small narrow footprints. 
